wikipedia_page.main: Charles Robert Wynn-Carington, 1st Marquess of Lincolnshire  (16 May 1843 – 13 June 1928), known as the Lord Carrington from 1868 to 1895, and as the Earl Carrington from 1895 to 1912, was a British Liberal politician and aristocrat. He was Governor of New South Wales from 1885 to 1890.
